The paper discusses privacy-preserving text analytics, which involves techniques from cryptography, machine learning, and data management. The focus is on constructing text processing applications that can operate on confidential text corpora without revealing sensitive information. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including cryptography (cs.CR), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), databases (cs.DB), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
